<h1>Chris Geirman</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.geirman.com/now/">geirman.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
San Diego
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Founder FrogQuest, React Native Mobile Developer
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I value one's right to choose what they do with their time and live that choice everyday deterministically
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I work for others as little as possible, and prioritize those things which I believe are worthy. I write software because I enjoy the challenges, the community, and the opportunities.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Giving truly is the greatest gift you receive in life and OSS
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Replay by Ken Grimmwood, best fiction I've ever read
</p>

